Create "Denied Cases by State" Shape Map 18

The map will be the last visual for our dashboard, so we are almost there.

STEP 1:

Before creating the map let us categorize "State" column to get an accurate outcome.

1.     Select "State" Column from the Foreign Workers Table

2.     Click On data category.

3.     Select “State or Province”.

4.     Enable Shape Map on your Power BI desktop by selecting File > Options and Settings > Options > Preview Features, then select the Shape Map Visual checkbox.

5.     You will need to restart Power BI Desktop after you make the selection, and you will now have the Shape Map Icon.



STEP 2: Create the Shape Map.

1.   Double click on the Shape Map icon on the visualization bar.

2.   Map visual will display on the report.

3.   Drag and drop the "State" column on the Location box.

4.   Drag and drop the "Denied Cases" column on the Color Saturation box

5.   Drag and drop the "# of Cases" column on the Tooltips box.



STEP 3: Configure the "Denied Cases by State" Visual

Part 1:

1.   Click on the Format icon.

2.   Fix the Map Size:  X Position: 0     Y position: 360   Weight: 640   Height: 358

3.   Fix the Data Color: Minimum: #D2D3D5    Maximum: B73A3A

4.   Fix the Map Zoom: Turn Auto Zoom: Off          Turn Zoom buttons: On.

5.   Fix the Title: Text: "Denied Cases by State"   Font Color: White    Background Color: #794548      Alignment: Center.

6.   Turn the Border: On    Color: White, 10% darker

7.     Your Shape Map should look as shown below. 



STEP 3:  Create the legend

  1. Go to your Data Colors.

  2. Take a screen shot of the color bar and save it.   

  3. Select Insert

  4. Select Image and load the color bar.

  5. Select Text Box 2 Times. Write "Low" on the first and “High" on the second.

      Turn the background: Off.  Font: Default and Color: Default

6. Align the Image and the High and Low Text Boxes. See final legend below.
